1
00:00:02,900 --> 00:00:05,119
There's nothing
particularly wrong with you

2
00:00:07,421 --> 00:00:08,790
I see.

3
00:00:08,956 --> 00:00:11,471
Can you tell me exactly
where you are hurting?

4
00:00:11,901 --> 00:00:15,669
This despair I felt
from this unexplainable pain...

5
00:00:27,435 --> 00:00:30,073
There's a bad spirit clinging onto you.

6
00:00:33,671 --> 00:00:35,671
You'll be in trouble.

7
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:38,000
It will cause a huge trouble.

8
00:00:38,413 --> 00:00:42,353
...I just want to try everything
to find an answer.

9
00:00:43,269 --> 00:00:46,135
I've tried everything
to cure this illness.

10
00:00:46,586 --> 00:00:49,192
I've used a talisman and
received exorcism dozens of times.

11
00:00:49,277 --> 00:00:50,585
A girl.

12
00:00:51,383 --> 00:00:52,773
A man.

13
00:00:53,358 --> 00:00:55,096
A child.

14
00:00:55,832 --> 00:00:57,010
An old lady.

15
00:00:59,639 --> 00:01:01,450
Evil spirits...

16
00:01:01,535 --> 00:01:05,718
...are residing inside your body.

17
00:01:06,059 --> 00:01:07,376
Go away!

18
00:01:08,254 --> 00:01:09,666
Go away!

19
00:01:10,311 --> 00:01:11,385
Get out!

20
00:01:11,621 --> 00:01:13,140
You're don't want to leave?

21
00:01:13,410 --> 00:01:14,445
Fine.

22
00:01:14,664 --> 00:01:15,692
Then, I will...

23
00:01:16,174 --> 00:01:19,449
...set you on fire!

24
00:01:19,901 --> 00:01:20,987
Go away.

25
00:01:21,442 --> 00:01:22,726
Go away!

26
00:01:27,692 --> 00:01:30,796
The longer I have to endure
this unexplainable pain...

27
00:01:31,070 --> 00:01:34,162
...the more I want to resent
something without any reason.

28
00:01:34,947 --> 00:01:36,242
For example...

29
00:01:36,338 --> 00:01:38,079
...a twist of fate...

30
00:01:45,797 --> 00:01:47,684
...if there's a God, then Him...

31
00:02:26,054 --> 00:02:27,788
...all of my mistakes...

32
00:02:29,323 --> 00:02:31,199
...or someone who loves me
unconditionally...

33
00:02:31,580 --> 00:02:33,751
...even if I despise them.

34
00:02:56,203 --> 00:02:57,724
What are you doing?

35
00:02:58,285 --> 00:02:59,362
Sleep.

36
00:03:00,726 --> 00:03:02,934
But you woke me up, Mom.

37
00:03:03,019 --> 00:03:05,494
You're the one who woke me up.

38
00:03:06,265 --> 00:03:08,768
Why did you work out
until you're all sore?

39
00:03:09,504 --> 00:03:11,736
I have no idea
what's wrong with your body.

40
00:03:12,890 --> 00:03:13,891
You're right.

41
00:03:14,689 --> 00:03:17,740
I'm curious to know
what's wrong with my body too.

42
00:03:19,105 --> 00:03:21,632
You should know best
since you gave birth to me.

43
00:03:22,599 --> 00:03:24,599
I told you to stop.

44
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:27,722
How can I stop?

45
00:03:28,725 --> 00:03:30,866
Whenever I hear you groan in pain...

46
00:03:31,135 --> 00:03:33,320
...my heart feels like it's about to drop.

47
00:03:34,852 --> 00:03:35,957
When you're sick...

48
00:03:37,042 --> 00:03:38,463
...I feel like it's my fault.

49
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:43,218
It's as if you're being punished,
for my mistakes.

50
00:03:44,888 --> 00:03:46,417
If I could...

51
00:03:46,967 --> 00:03:48,480
...I want the pain to
be transferred to me.

52
00:03:51,026 --> 00:03:53,026
Do you even know how I feel?

53
00:03:53,445 --> 00:03:55,376
That day, I made my mind...

54
00:03:56,368 --> 00:03:59,011
...that I'll never be my mom's punishment.

55
00:04:00,188 --> 00:04:01,236
That I'll never...

56
00:04:02,309 --> 00:04:06,183
...tell her about this horrible condition.

57
00:04:06,530 --> 00:04:07,675
So if I can..

58
00:04:08,241 --> 00:04:09,658
...I'll never tell her
for the rest of my life.

59
00:04:09,743 --> 00:04:12,179
Han Segye, your mom is here.

60
00:04:12,489 --> 00:04:13,502
Mom?

61
00:04:14,319 --> 00:04:15,417
Mrs. Han.

62
00:04:30,860 --> 00:04:32,042
Who's this?

63
00:04:33,441 --> 00:04:37,517
I did not plan to get caught
in this situation.

64
00:04:38,447 --> 00:04:39,938
He's my nephew.

65
00:04:42,417 --> 00:04:45,724
He must really miss his mom
that he suddenly called for his mom.

66
00:04:45,809 --> 00:04:46,704
Your nephew?

67
00:04:47,439 --> 00:04:48,766
But you're an only child.

68
00:04:52,007 --> 00:04:53,104
He's my sworn sister's

69
00:04:53,233 --> 00:04:56,468
Mrs. Han, do you know about sworn sisters?

70
00:04:56,577 --> 00:04:58,298
-Were you a bully at school?
-No.

71
00:04:58,383 --> 00:04:59,520
No. That's not what I mean.

72
00:05:01,847 --> 00:05:03,762
I'm actually grooming him
to become an actor.

73
00:05:03,847 --> 00:05:05,420
I thought you said
he's your sworn sister's son.

74
00:05:05,505 --> 00:05:06,915
That's right.

75
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:10,181
I'm younger than my sworn sister.

76
00:05:10,463 --> 00:05:12,065
To sum it all up...

77
00:05:12,748 --> 00:05:15,424
...she's not feeling so well nowadays...

78
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:17,679
...so she's at the hospital.

79
00:05:17,764 --> 00:05:20,003
Where's his father?
Why do you have to take care of him?

80
00:05:22,139 --> 00:05:23,343
Well...

81
00:05:23,754 --> 00:05:26,202
Actually, she is...

82
00:05:27,014 --> 00:05:28,535
...a single mom.

83
00:05:29,756 --> 00:05:32,689
Geez. Men only cause troubles
but never actually take responsibility.

84
00:05:34,239 --> 00:05:36,602
When you grow up, you should
find your dad and avenge him.

85
00:05:36,687 --> 00:05:37,727
I'll help you.

86
00:05:38,681 --> 00:05:40,144
Gosh. My mom...

87
00:05:40,348 --> 00:05:41,687
...can be quite aggressive.

88
00:05:44,039 --> 00:05:46,971
Still, you can't just bring a kid
in and out of this place.

89
00:05:47,056 --> 00:05:48,938
This is how the rumors start.

90
00:05:49,023 --> 00:05:52,247
Don't worry.
I hid him before bringing him in.

91
00:05:52,645 --> 00:05:56,091
Now, I just need to hide him again
when I leave the house.

92
00:05:56,176 --> 00:05:58,766
-Where's Segye?
-She has a shooting outside the city.

93
00:05:58,851 --> 00:05:59,890
Then, why are you here?

94
00:05:59,975 --> 00:06:01,975
I'm just stopping by
to pick up some stuff.

95
00:06:02,810 --> 00:06:04,810
Oh no. We're late.

96
00:06:05,175 --> 00:06:06,407
We should get going.

97
00:06:06,492 --> 00:06:08,271
Let's go.

98
00:06:09,855 --> 00:06:11,130
You can leave him here.

99
00:06:16,254 --> 00:06:18,254
Leave him here. I can look after him.

100
00:06:18,396 --> 00:06:19,953
You're bringing him to the shoot?

101
00:06:20,155 --> 00:06:21,341
That'll spread the rumor even more.

102
00:06:21,779 --> 00:06:25,063
I'll keep him company in the house,
so just come back as soon as you're done.

103
00:06:26,229 --> 00:06:28,575
You're okay with staying here
with me, right?

104
00:06:28,725 --> 00:06:31,704
No, I'm not okay with that.

105
00:06:32,114 --> 00:06:32,976
Well...

106
00:06:33,743 --> 00:06:36,602
You don't really have to do that.

107
00:06:36,687 --> 00:06:38,792
How can you work and
take care of him at the same time?

108
00:06:39,023 --> 00:06:42,067
I'll look after him,
you just take care of my daughter.

109
00:06:42,567 --> 00:06:44,728
Well, you see...

110
00:06:45,164 --> 00:06:46,886
-The thing is, he's very...
-Come here.

111
00:06:55,786 --> 00:06:57,904
Say goodbye to your aunt.

112
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,145
Say "Bye, Aunt Woomi".

113
00:07:02,179 --> 00:07:03,626
Aunt Woomi...

114
00:07:04,943 --> 00:07:06,092
...bye.

115
00:07:09,103 --> 00:07:09,946
I'll pray...

116
00:07:10,533 --> 00:07:12,057
...for your safety.

117
00:07:12,585 --> 00:07:14,062
You'll come and save me, right?

118
00:07:16,584 --> 00:07:18,483
People will think you're his child.

119
00:07:18,738 --> 00:07:20,966
Why is your farewell so depressing?

120
00:07:40,463 --> 00:07:41,390
Let's go inside.

121
00:07:44,715 --> 00:07:45,796
My friend...

122
00:07:46,310 --> 00:07:48,702
...please don't forget me
who you're leaving behind.

123
00:07:59,682 --> 00:08:01,963
My future seems bleak...

124
00:08:02,059 --> 00:08:04,188
...and my blood is boiling.

125
00:08:12,309 --> 00:08:13,500
Here you go.

126
00:08:13,654 --> 00:08:14,669
Let's have a bite.

127
00:08:16,857 --> 00:08:18,140
What's your name?

128
00:08:18,303 --> 00:08:19,177
Se...

129
00:08:21,376 --> 00:08:22,210
Se?

130
00:08:23,083 --> 00:08:24,012
It's Woojoo.

131
00:08:24,109 --> 00:08:25,249
Se Woojoo?

132
00:08:26,012 --> 00:08:27,713
My name is Seo Woojoo.

133
00:08:29,437 --> 00:08:30,513
All right.

134
00:08:32,659 --> 00:08:34,134
Woojoo, do you like this?

135
00:08:41,186 --> 00:08:44,910
My daughter also loves this dish
when she was your age.

136
00:08:45,472 --> 00:08:47,428
But back then, I didn't have much money.

137
00:08:47,513 --> 00:08:49,203
So I can only feed her vegetables.

138
00:08:49,831 --> 00:08:51,739
The thought of it still breaks my heart.

139
00:08:56,303 --> 00:08:58,596
Gosh. Look at you.

140
00:08:59,020 --> 00:09:01,117
You're looking at me
as if you know how it feels.

141
00:09:03,383 --> 00:09:05,263
But strangely enough...

142
00:09:06,055 --> 00:09:07,640
...I kind of like this.

143
00:09:07,725 --> 00:09:09,188
Here. Eat up.

144
00:09:23,243 --> 00:09:24,644
I can do it on my own.

145
00:09:27,045 --> 00:09:29,182
Kids these days grow up so quick.

146
00:09:29,524 --> 00:09:32,789
Segye still couldn't go to the bathroom
on her own at that age.

147
00:09:34,444 --> 00:09:36,685
I can't answer your call right now. I'm...

148
00:09:37,232 --> 00:09:38,158
It's that day.

149
00:09:38,344 --> 00:09:39,186
Should I go there now?

150
00:09:39,271 --> 00:09:40,697
No. Don't come.

151
00:09:40,863 --> 00:09:41,705
Why?

152
00:09:41,801 --> 00:09:43,024
Who did you turn into this time?

153
00:09:43,559 --> 00:09:44,525
It's okay.

154
00:09:44,781 --> 00:09:46,163
I can still recognize you.

155
00:09:46,248 --> 00:09:49,123
That's exactly why.
I'm scared that you'd recognize me.

156
00:09:49,208 --> 00:09:51,549
My pride is the last thing
I'm hanging on to.

157
00:09:52,183 --> 00:09:54,251
You're making me more curious
when you say it like that.

158
00:09:54,587 --> 00:09:56,587
Do you remember the third clause
in our contract?

159
00:09:56,672 --> 00:09:58,672
"Respond to calls actively..."

160
00:09:58,836 --> 00:10:01,106
"... and show a cooperative attitude."

161
00:10:01,191 --> 00:10:03,708
I'll call you when I need you.
Just be on standby until then.

162
00:10:04,027 --> 00:10:05,380
I thought you said not to come.

163
00:10:05,656 --> 00:10:07,974
That's why only come when I need you.

164
00:10:08,266 --> 00:10:10,239
Just in case, take your phone to bed.

165
00:10:10,324 --> 00:10:12,117
You need to help me keep my secret.

166
00:10:12,345 --> 00:10:14,509
If you don't, I'm going to sue
you for breach of contract.

167
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:18,284
Who are you keeping your secret from?

168
00:10:18,369 --> 00:10:20,257
Woojoo, are you okay?

169
00:10:20,659 --> 00:10:21,589
Does your tummy hurt a lot?

170
00:10:21,674 --> 00:10:23,484
I'm out of time. I need to go.

171
00:10:23,661 --> 00:10:25,263
Don't contact me for the time being.

172
00:10:26,199 --> 00:10:27,642
I'm done.

173
00:10:27,898 --> 00:10:29,468
(Don't contact me for the time being)

174
00:10:32,486 --> 00:10:33,377
Did I...

175
00:10:34,204 --> 00:10:35,044
...just get dumped?

176
00:10:35,129 --> 00:10:36,956
I'm glad to hear that.

177
00:10:37,041 --> 00:10:38,823
Just go check on your fish.

178
00:10:45,156 --> 00:10:46,835
I've come up with a name for this one.

179
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:50,773
I don't want to hear it.

180
00:10:51,346 --> 00:10:53,660
-Why not?
-Because it's going to be obvious.

181
00:10:57,249 --> 00:10:59,264
The loser will buy coffee
for everyone. Okay?

182
00:10:59,349 --> 00:11:00,701
-Okay.
-Okay.

183
00:11:02,012 --> 00:11:03,113
Fold your finger if you're a man.

184
00:11:03,673 --> 00:11:05,610
Fold your finger if you're over 35.

185
00:11:06,618 --> 00:11:08,358
Fold your finger if you're
a team leader or higher.

186
00:11:08,443 --> 00:11:09,526
-Just fold a finger.
-Hurry up.

187
00:11:09,611 --> 00:11:12,080
Wow. You guys are playing this
the dirty way, aren't you?

188
00:11:12,417 --> 00:11:14,267
Fold your finger if you're
below the team leader.

189
00:11:15,894 --> 00:11:17,836
Fold your finger if your hair
doesn't reach your shoulders.

190
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:21,720
Fold your finger
if your ears are not pierced.

191
00:11:22,552 --> 00:11:24,858
Aren't you guys being too petty?

192
00:11:24,943 --> 00:11:27,601
You're obviously targeting me.
Are you not?

193
00:11:28,062 --> 00:11:29,883
What's going on?
Why didn't you fold your finger?

194
00:11:31,513 --> 00:11:32,977
You have an ear piercing?

195
00:11:33,089 --> 00:11:34,885
I had one last weekend.

196
00:11:35,276 --> 00:11:37,240
What kind of man has their ears pierced?

197
00:11:37,325 --> 00:11:38,769
Gosh, you're so outdated.

198
00:11:38,854 --> 00:11:40,933
Who doesn't pierce their ears nowadays?

199
00:11:41,018 --> 00:11:43,298
That person is right here.

200
00:11:43,383 --> 00:11:45,842
Team Leader, please go buy us some coffee.

201
00:11:45,927 --> 00:11:48,906
This is invalid.
You guys colluded against me.

202
00:11:48,991 --> 00:11:49,966
That's why...

203
00:11:50,158 --> 00:11:53,031
...you should've paid more
attention to your staff.

204
00:11:53,116 --> 00:11:55,891
How am I supposed to notice
he pierced his ear?

205
00:11:55,976 --> 00:11:57,488
I bet even Mr. Seo doesn't notice it.

206
00:11:57,573 --> 00:11:59,088
What are you talking about?

207
00:11:59,172 --> 00:12:02,629
Mr. Seo notices every single tiny detail.

208
00:12:03,039 --> 00:12:04,524
Do you want to bet on it? 50,000 won?

209
00:12:04,630 --> 00:12:05,369
-Sure.
-I'm in.

210
00:12:05,454 --> 00:12:06,799
-I'm in.
-Okay.

211
00:12:12,478 --> 00:12:14,478
Good morning, Mr. Seo.

212
00:12:16,995 --> 00:12:18,667
Hello, Mr. Seo.

213
00:12:18,770 --> 00:12:19,683
Hi.

214
00:12:19,857 --> 00:12:21,806
Looks like you're taking a break.

215
00:12:22,335 --> 00:12:24,117
It's important to take a break from work.

216
00:12:24,884 --> 00:12:25,745
Excuse me, then.

217
00:12:31,662 --> 00:12:32,559
By the way,

218
00:12:35,631 --> 00:12:37,354
Jang Minhee, did you
have your ears pierced?

219
00:12:41,057 --> 00:12:41,911
Yes.

220
00:12:42,573 --> 00:12:45,023
-Nice!
-I know Mr. Seo will never let us down.

221
00:12:45,475 --> 00:12:48,088
Team Leader, give us our 50,000 won now.

222
00:12:48,173 --> 00:12:51,287
You're not helping me at all.

223
00:12:53,049 --> 00:12:54,009
What's wrong with you?

224
00:12:54,809 --> 00:12:56,398
Oh my god, what is this feeling?

225
00:12:56,771 --> 00:12:57,672
My heart is fluttering.

226
00:13:03,189 --> 00:13:04,564
I forgot my wallet.

227
00:13:05,165 --> 00:13:06,372
You pay.

228
00:13:07,279 --> 00:13:09,775
I'll take everything from here to here.

229
00:13:10,852 --> 00:13:13,118
I take it back when I said
I kind of like this.

230
00:13:13,672 --> 00:13:16,011
That feeling only lasted one day.

231
00:13:16,785 --> 00:13:18,567
Now that I've been
stuck here for two days...

232
00:13:19,560 --> 00:13:21,008
...I'm starting to get crazy.

233
00:13:25,162 --> 00:13:27,508
Watch the TV while drinking that.

234
00:13:28,110 --> 00:13:30,110
Don't sit too close to the TV.

235
00:13:33,230 --> 00:13:35,346
Geez. Who does she think I am?

236
00:13:37,612 --> 00:13:38,458
Wait...

237
00:13:39,031 --> 00:13:40,594
This tastes better than I expected.

238
00:13:43,411 --> 00:13:47,008
But I feel a little bit of suspense.

239
00:13:49,984 --> 00:13:51,068
Day three.

240
00:13:52,164 --> 00:13:53,647
I want to be alone.

241
00:14:01,477 --> 00:14:02,518
What's wrong?

242
00:14:02,670 --> 00:14:03,845
You can't fall asleep?

243
00:14:07,034 --> 00:14:11,030
You've stayed with me for three days now.
Do you still feel uncomfortable?

244
00:14:11,620 --> 00:14:12,907
Absolutely.

245
00:14:13,357 --> 00:14:15,285
I'm very uncomfortable.

246
00:14:16,322 --> 00:14:18,481
It's probably been 10 years...

247
00:14:18,973 --> 00:14:20,710
...since I've lain next to you.

248
00:14:33,830 --> 00:14:35,322
But...

249
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:38,875
...it does feel kind of relaxing.

250
00:15:19,315 --> 00:15:20,519
Long time no see, Eunho.

251
00:15:23,012 --> 00:15:24,225
I'm back.

252
00:15:28,882 --> 00:15:31,323
Wash your hands and have a sit.

253
00:15:32,608 --> 00:15:34,017
-Go.
-Hurry up. Go to your room.

254
00:15:43,576 --> 00:15:46,176
The rice taste extra delicious today.

255
00:15:49,598 --> 00:15:52,631
Mom, the seasoned vegetables are perfect.

256
00:15:56,147 --> 00:15:57,544
I'll do the dishes.

257
00:15:59,941 --> 00:16:01,200
Sure. Why not.

258
00:16:27,998 --> 00:16:30,360
(2019 Seminary Admission Guide)

259
00:17:48,419 --> 00:17:52,266
Why is Mom cleaning
so early in the morning?

260
00:17:52,974 --> 00:17:53,849
My photo room.

261
00:17:54,288 --> 00:17:55,279
My dressing room.

262
00:18:06,625 --> 00:18:08,217
Are you going to keep
sitting on that chair?

263
00:18:08,317 --> 00:18:09,826
-No.
-Why not?

264
00:18:10,256 --> 00:18:12,896
It suits you very well.
Do some of my work while you're at it.

265
00:18:12,981 --> 00:18:15,540
I'm already doing a lot of your work.

