00:37:13,097 --> 00:37:14,628
I like it too.

539
00:37:21,344 --> 00:37:22,729
Do you think Minjun...

540
00:37:22,923 --> 00:37:25,118
...will keep on liking it?

541
00:37:28,135 --> 00:37:29,747
When he's 15...

542
00:37:30,024 --> 00:37:31,851
...he may not like it anymore.

543
00:37:33,681 --> 00:37:34,888
By the time he's 20...

544
00:37:36,198 --> 00:37:37,977
...he may not like it anymore.

545
00:37:38,879 --> 00:37:40,132
Or when he's 30...

546
00:37:42,526 --> 00:37:44,204
...he may not like it anymore.

547
00:37:49,351 --> 00:37:50,934
But I won't know that.

548
00:37:54,280 --> 00:37:56,209
I'll probably never find out.

549
00:38:05,578 --> 00:38:07,640
I'll think of him every time I see this.

550
00:38:12,184 --> 00:38:13,762
And that breaks my heart,

551
00:38:17,893 --> 00:38:19,286
but it also makes me happy.

552
00:38:24,125 --> 00:38:28,276
What kind of consolation can I offer
to a grieving mother who lost her child?

553
00:38:29,351 --> 00:38:31,098
The only thing I can do...

554
00:38:40,034 --> 00:38:41,482
It's delicious.

555
00:38:43,495 --> 00:38:45,002
For now, I like it.

556
00:38:51,049 --> 00:38:53,175
...is this.

557
00:39:45,588 --> 00:39:47,065
See you in a while.

558
00:39:47,491 --> 00:39:49,567
It's almost time
for the magic to be lifted.

559
00:39:50,053 --> 00:39:51,779
I'm going to keep looking at you.

560
00:40:02,963 --> 00:40:05,117
I'm sorry to have caused you
so much trouble,

561
00:40:06,392 --> 00:40:08,547
by having an unusual girlfriend like me.

562
00:40:08,931 --> 00:40:10,431
Why must you be so kind?

563
00:40:10,880 --> 00:40:12,590
It's tiring to become your boyfriend.

564
00:40:13,176 --> 00:40:15,167
There's nothing I can do about it.
It's part of my charm.

565
00:40:15,252 --> 00:40:16,211
You just have to accept it.

566
00:40:18,657 --> 00:40:20,945
I took too much of your time
when you have work to do.

567
00:40:21,192 --> 00:40:22,882
I rather quit my job,

568
00:40:22,967 --> 00:40:24,845
and follow you around.

569
00:40:25,683 --> 00:40:27,107
I know you're not going to do that.

570
00:40:29,021 --> 00:40:30,280
But it's nice to hear.

571
00:41:00,314 --> 00:41:01,293
I have a delivery for you.

572
00:41:09,887 --> 00:41:11,451
You're Ms. Kang Sara, right?

573
00:41:13,009 --> 00:41:15,174
Mr. Kang Daeshik sent you flowers.

574
00:41:20,053 --> 00:41:21,533
Please sign here.

575
00:41:29,428 --> 00:41:30,813
Thank you. Enjoy the rest of your day.

576
00:41:56,898 --> 00:41:58,691
Happy birthday, my dear daughter.

577
00:41:59,219 --> 00:42:02,874
Marigolds grow well
no matter where they are.

578
00:42:02,959 --> 00:42:05,511
You just need to give them
enough sunlight and fresh air.

579
00:42:06,389 --> 00:42:09,027
Every time I see marigolds
blooming somewhere...

580
00:42:09,153 --> 00:42:10,731
...I'm reminded of you.

581
00:42:11,337 --> 00:42:13,243
Thank you for growing up so well.

582
00:42:14,123 --> 00:42:15,345
P.S.

583
00:42:15,757 --> 00:42:17,649
Marigolds symbolize...

584
00:42:17,804 --> 00:42:20,483
...happiness that is bound to happen.

585
00:42:21,358 --> 00:42:23,505
I'm sure you'll find your happiness.

586
00:42:24,070 --> 00:42:25,223
From Dad.

587
00:42:26,805 --> 00:42:28,317
It's my birthday today.

588
00:43:05,137 --> 00:43:07,063
Are you really choosing this path?

589
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:12,282
It will not be easy.

590
00:43:13,293 --> 00:43:14,592
I'm aware.

591
00:43:17,148 --> 00:43:18,097
All right.

592
00:43:18,601 --> 00:43:20,727
Then, I will pray for you.

593
00:43:33,782 --> 00:43:36,128
In the name of the Father, and of the Son,
and of the Holy Spirit.

594
00:43:36,213 --> 00:43:38,694
Dear Merciful Lord.

595
00:43:39,623 --> 00:43:42,771
Please listen to my desperate prayer.

596
00:43:43,035 --> 00:43:45,302
Please protect my parents...

597
00:43:45,796 --> 00:43:47,796
...whose hearts have been broken
by this sinner.

598
00:43:48,435 --> 00:43:51,079
Please heal my friend, Segye.

599
00:43:52,427 --> 00:43:55,839
Please send my friend, Woomi, a good man.

600
00:43:57,514 --> 00:43:59,704
And finally, to the pitiful and lonely...

601
00:44:00,439 --> 00:44:02,698
I don't normally tell
these things to others.

602
00:44:03,624 --> 00:44:04,819
But why did I just do that?

603
00:44:05,205 --> 00:44:06,767
Because I listen to you.

604
00:44:07,593 --> 00:44:10,280
It's because all this time,
you didn't have anyone who listens.

605
00:44:11,873 --> 00:44:14,052
Please make sure the pitiful and lonely...

606
00:44:14,490 --> 00:44:15,481
...person...

607
00:44:16,058 --> 00:44:18,707
...eats three meals a day.

608
00:44:20,347 --> 00:44:23,277
In the name of the Father, and of the Son,
and of the Holy Spirit.

609
00:44:24,540 --> 00:44:25,465
Amen.

610
00:45:34,543 --> 00:45:36,478
What's this?
You didn't tell me you're coming.

611
00:45:36,563 --> 00:45:37,963
This is my home.

612
00:45:39,245 --> 00:45:41,660
What about you? You didn't even call
to tell me you're coming.

613
00:45:47,992 --> 00:45:50,149
Oh my. What's wrong with you?

614
00:45:51,783 --> 00:45:53,102
I missed you.

615
00:45:55,351 --> 00:45:56,334
A lot.

616
00:45:59,033 --> 00:46:00,286
A whole lot.

617
00:46:10,252 --> 00:46:12,164
I met your boyfriend.

618
00:46:12,249 --> 00:46:13,468
I know.

619
00:46:14,091 --> 00:46:17,553
I said "boyfriend", not "ex-boyfriend".
But you don't seem to care.

620
00:46:18,261 --> 00:46:19,375
Are you still seeing him?

621
00:46:20,753 --> 00:46:22,325
No. I just got used to it.

622
00:46:22,410 --> 00:46:24,223
He seemed like a nice person.

623
00:46:25,028 --> 00:46:26,634
He said he wants to date you again.

624
00:46:28,904 --> 00:46:29,952
Han Segye...

625
00:46:30,227 --> 00:46:31,594
...did you hear me?

626
00:46:33,927 --> 00:46:34,725
What did you say?

627
00:46:34,810 --> 00:46:36,698
I'm telling you to marry him.

628
00:46:36,793 --> 00:46:37,971
Seo Dojae.

629
00:46:38,302 --> 00:46:39,393
What did you say?

630
00:46:39,507 --> 00:46:40,919
You heard me just fine.

631
00:46:41,289 --> 00:46:42,883
Are you going to keep
pretending you didn't hear me?

632
00:46:42,968 --> 00:46:45,401
If you're going to talk
about marriage, then go home.

633
00:46:51,067 --> 00:46:51,910
Here.

634
00:46:54,431 --> 00:46:56,325
Think about your age.

635
00:46:56,742 --> 00:46:58,138
You should have a baby soon.

636
00:46:58,223 --> 00:47:00,136
-I'm not going to.
-Why not?

637
00:47:00,221 --> 00:47:01,926
I don't want one. It's scary.

638
00:47:04,056 --> 00:47:05,612
What if my child gets sick?

639
00:47:07,053 --> 00:47:08,381
Who's going to take responsibility?

640
00:47:09,222 --> 00:47:11,968
Why are you so pessimistic?

641
00:47:14,215 --> 00:47:16,091
You're going to need
a place to go back to.

642
00:47:16,281 --> 00:47:17,913
So you need to have a family.

643
00:47:17,998 --> 00:47:19,047
I don't care.

644
00:47:20,105 --> 00:47:21,055
I already have you.

645
00:47:34,173 --> 00:47:35,008
Mom.

646
00:47:36,110 --> 00:47:39,008
How would you feel
if my appearance changes?

647
00:47:39,495 --> 00:47:40,381
Why?

648
00:47:41,000 --> 00:47:42,647
Did someone say you're ugly?

649
00:47:43,217 --> 00:47:44,230
Did they say you're different?

650
00:47:44,315 --> 00:47:45,982
No. It's nothing like that.

651
00:47:47,857 --> 00:47:49,503
Don't mind them.

652
00:47:49,910 --> 00:47:51,488
You just live your life.

653
00:47:52,740 --> 00:47:54,582
It's enough as long as
I understand you...

654
00:47:54,798 --> 00:47:56,487
...and you understand yourself.

655
00:47:58,288 --> 00:48:01,848
You should shower yourself with love
every moment.

656
00:48:02,298 --> 00:48:03,321
Like me.

657
00:48:05,590 --> 00:48:07,784
I didn't expect that to come from you.

658
00:48:08,658 --> 00:48:10,351
Why don't you want to get married?

659
00:48:10,700 --> 00:48:12,667
He seemed like a good person to me.

660
00:48:14,690 --> 00:48:16,413
Is he a player?

661
00:48:16,498 --> 00:48:17,416
Is that why?

662
00:48:17,505 --> 00:48:20,023
I dumped him. Because he was
getting in the way of my career.

663
00:48:22,160 --> 00:48:24,206
He likes to follow me around.

664
00:48:25,450 --> 00:48:26,970
He's too nice...

665
00:48:27,804 --> 00:48:29,223
...and pitiful.

666
00:48:30,399 --> 00:48:31,720
Plus, I really like him.

667
00:48:33,671 --> 00:48:34,524
So it's not good.

668
00:48:34,749 --> 00:48:35,661
Segye...

669
00:48:36,486 --> 00:48:37,936
...you're seeing him, right?

670
00:48:38,076 --> 00:48:39,448
I told you, I'm not.

671
00:48:39,533 --> 00:48:40,469
Is his family against it?

672
00:48:40,554 --> 00:48:42,097
I'm against it. Me.

673
00:48:42,487 --> 00:48:44,080
Your daughter is an actress.

674
00:48:44,165 --> 00:48:46,303
Can't you see me taking care of myself
even at this moment?

675
00:48:47,271 --> 00:48:49,273
There are not enough lead roles as is.

676
00:48:49,358 --> 00:48:50,238
How can I get married?

677
00:48:50,323 --> 00:48:52,222
You're my daughter
before you're an actress.

678
00:48:52,769 --> 00:48:54,225
You're so ambitious.

679
00:48:54,384 --> 00:48:56,147
Why do you have to work so hard?

680
00:48:56,464 --> 00:48:58,951
I'm afraid I might
suddenly disappear one day.

681
00:48:59,234 --> 00:49:00,873
What are you talking about?

682
00:49:01,841 --> 00:49:04,040
I'm bound to die one day, aren't I?

683
00:49:04,262 --> 00:49:06,262
I want you to watch movies...

684
00:49:06,386 --> 00:49:09,994
...and think about how pretty
and good of an actor I am.

685
00:49:10,611 --> 00:49:12,172
This is nonsense.

686
00:49:12,735 --> 00:49:14,387
Get married before you die.

687
00:49:14,472 --> 00:49:16,009
I told you, I'm not going to.

688
00:49:23,419 --> 00:49:26,148
I'm going. Don't forget to eat
the side dishes in the fridge.

689
00:49:26,233 --> 00:49:27,196
Okay.

690
00:49:27,355 --> 00:49:30,611
I've also put herbal tonics in the fridge,
so make sure to drink them regularly.

691
00:49:30,696 --> 00:49:33,217
They'll make me gain weight. I'm not
going to drink them. Stop buying them.

692
00:49:33,302 --> 00:49:35,302
I got ones that won't make
you gain weight, you brat.

693
00:49:35,564 --> 00:49:36,684
Drink them.

694
00:49:36,769 --> 00:49:38,667
I bought them because
I'm worried about your health

695
00:49:38,942 --> 00:49:39,872
Fine.

696
00:49:40,369 --> 00:49:42,483
Don't drink too much.

697
00:49:42,663 --> 00:49:44,470
Be good to Woomi and Eunho.

698
00:49:44,628 --> 00:49:47,312
Put your socks into
the laundry basket right away.

699
00:49:47,751 --> 00:49:49,042
Am I a kid?

700
00:49:49,582 --> 00:49:52,020
If you're that worried about me,
you should stay here longer.

701
00:49:52,136 --> 00:49:53,140
I can't.

702
00:49:53,325 --> 00:49:55,034
I have to water my plants.

703
00:49:55,119 --> 00:49:56,741
Are your plants more important than me?

704
00:49:56,826 --> 00:49:58,291
Of course, you brat.

705
00:49:58,590 --> 00:50:02,453
They can't move on their own.
Imagine how thirsty they are.

706
00:50:02,862 --> 00:50:05,169
Fine. Go. Get going.

707
00:50:05,286 --> 00:50:06,601
I'm going somewhere too.

708
00:50:07,341 --> 00:50:08,526
Where are you going?

709
00:50:17,490 --> 00:50:18,514
She's not here.

710
00:50:20,530 --> 00:50:21,871
Is it a good thing?

711
00:50:22,548 --> 00:50:23,535
Of course, it is.

712
00:50:25,782 --> 00:50:27,492
Did we do the right thing?

713
00:50:30,105 --> 00:50:31,357
We lied to her.

714
00:50:33,611 --> 00:50:34,661
Who knows?

715
00:50:35,810 --> 00:50:37,225
I'm not sure about that.

716
00:50:37,702 --> 00:50:38,613
But...

717
00:50:40,888 --> 00:50:42,448
...I think your lie...

718
00:50:42,993 --> 00:50:44,876
...gave her a will to live.

719
00:50:46,093 --> 00:50:46,997
Most probably.

720
00:50:54,448 --> 00:50:55,928
Geez. Seriously.

721
00:50:56,859 --> 00:50:57,864
I like you so much.

722
00:50:58,356 --> 00:50:59,507
Are you talking about me?

723
00:51:00,113 --> 00:51:00,961
Yes.

724
00:51:04,579 --> 00:51:05,687
I have to go now.

725
00:51:05,772 --> 00:51:06,765
Already?

726
00:51:07,296 --> 00:51:08,427
I haven't seen you in a while.

727
00:51:08,512 --> 00:51:11,128
What do you mean? We met yesterday.

728
00:51:11,213 --> 00:51:12,623
You said you were seeing me.

729
00:51:12,708 --> 00:51:13,933
Well, that's...

730
00:51:14,714 --> 00:51:15,606
I have to hurry.

731
00:51:15,691 --> 00:51:16,734
Where are you going?

732
00:51:19,030 --> 00:51:21,310
I have a very important appointment.

733
00:51:31,410 --> 00:51:32,615
Thank you.

734
00:51:41,770 --> 00:51:43,486
What are you doing? Have a seat.

735
00:51:43,771 --> 00:51:45,302
Han Segye, what are you doing here?

736
00:51:46,028 --> 00:51:47,923
I invited her over.

737
00:51:48,008 --> 00:51:52,056
Your mom really wanted
to have a meal with her.

738
00:51:52,265 --> 00:51:55,436
So I asked for a special favor from her.

739
00:51:56,022 --> 00:51:58,481
She's not your guest. She's mine.

740
00:51:58,837 --> 00:51:59,974
Come, take a seat.

741
00:52:00,916 --> 00:52:02,960
You should've told me beforehand.

742
00:52:03,315 --> 00:52:04,900
Either of you.

743
00:52:05,223 --> 00:52:06,578
Surprise...

744
00:52:06,682 --> 00:52:09,071
I'm sorry, I'm late. I had to finish...

745
00:52:09,156 --> 00:52:10,368
Hello.

746
00:52:13,828 --> 00:52:15,289
I see we have a guest.

747
00:52:18,684 --> 00:52:19,741
Hello.

748
00:52:29,310 --> 00:52:32,651
Seeing Dojae and Segye
sitting next to each other,

749
00:52:32,736 --> 00:52:34,948
I feel like I have my appetite back.

750
00:52:35,033 --> 00:52:37,530
They look like a perfect couple.

751
00:52:37,641 --> 00:52:38,550
Don't you think so, Dad?

752
00:52:38,635 --> 00:52:41,739
If your daughter says so,
then I must agree.

753
00:52:44,134 --> 00:52:46,684
It makes me so happy...

754
00:52:46,817 --> 00:52:49,640
...to see you smile widely like this.

755
00:52:51,509 --> 00:52:54,592
It was Sara's birthday not too long ago.

756
00:52:55,079 --> 00:52:55,935
Oh my.

757
00:52:56,174 --> 00:52:57,154
It was?

758
00:52:57,456 --> 00:52:58,858
Why didn't you say anything?

759
00:53:00,144 --> 00:53:01,115
Secretary Kim!

760
00:53:01,353 --> 00:53:02,892
Secretary Kim, where are you?

761
00:53:02,977 --> 00:53:07,572
He should've reported to me
if it was a family member's birthday.

762
00:53:07,657 --> 00:53:10,668
I'm sorry I didn't congratulate you
when I'm your mother.

763
00:53:10,753 --> 00:53:12,215
It's okay.

764
00:53:12,981 --> 00:53:15,899
It's been a while
since we had a family gathering.

765
00:53:15,984 --> 00:53:18,126
I'm happy enough to be here with you.

766
00:53:22,792 --> 00:53:24,025
Happy birthday.

767
00:53:32,164 --> 00:53:33,171
Thank you.

768
00:53:33,774 --> 00:53:35,253
I really didn't expect...

769
00:53:35,790 --> 00:53:37,204
...to receive a gift.

770
00:53:37,315 --> 00:53:38,474
It's nothing much.

771
00:53:38,992 --> 00:53:41,826
You already have everything
you can wish for.

772
00:53:56,176 --> 00:53:58,706
(How to laugh and get angry at the fools)

773
00:54:01,606 --> 00:54:04,637
(How to laugh and get angry at the fools)

774
00:54:07,366 --> 00:54:08,478
I like it.

775
00:54:08,782 --> 00:54:10,099
I knew you would.

776
00:54:10,441 --> 00:54:13,053
If I had known,
I would have also brought a gift.

777
00:54:14,647 --> 00:54:17,539
You being here is already a gift for me.

778
00:54:20,052 --> 00:54:21,463
I heard you broke up.

779
00:54:21,755 --> 00:54:23,434
Are you back together?

780
00:54:24,690 --> 00:54:27,229
No. I'm here on Chairman Im's invitation.

781
00:54:29,158 --> 00:54:30,057
I figured.

782
00:54:31,343 --> 00:54:33,521
You made such a fuss when you broke up.

783
00:54:34,194 --> 00:54:36,155
It's not right to get
back together this soon.

784
00:54:41,460 --> 00:54:43,181
Director Kim said this once,

785
00:54:44,089 --> 00:54:47,295
"This is why I can't
really respect the family."

786
00:54:48,975 --> 00:54:50,648
I was angry when I first heard it,

787
00:54:51,201 --> 00:54:53,021
but after I think about it again,

788
00:54:53,283 --> 00:54:55,561
I shouldn't have been.

789
00:54:56,412 --> 00:54:59,786
Acting too thoughtlessly
can also be a problem.

790
00:55:00,868 --> 00:55:03,063
Thank you for worrying about a problem...

791
00:55:03,544 --> 00:55:05,552
-...that didn't happen.
-Don't mention it.

792
00:55:08,360 --> 00:55:09,435
The food is delicious.

793
00:55:15,217 --> 00:55:19,323
There seem to be a lot of men
who do housework these days.

794
00:55:19,876 --> 00:55:23,945
It's probably because house chores
are too hard, right?

795
00:55:44,225 --> 00:55:45,282
Han Segye.

796
00:55:51,351 --> 00:55:52,834
I didn't expect you to do it,

797
00:55:53,107 --> 00:55:54,344
but you played dirty.

798
00:55:55,480 --> 00:55:56,544
Kang Sara.

799
00:55:56,948 --> 00:55:57,961
It's fine.

800
00:56:01,110 --> 00:56:03,395
I don't know why you didn't
expect me to do that.

801
00:56:04,181 --> 00:56:06,557
But I'm someone
who gives back what I received.

802
00:56:07,024 --> 00:56:08,634
Are you done talking?

803
00:56:11,106 --> 00:56:11,974
You've got some nerve.

804
00:56:12,059 --> 00:56:13,424
I'm not done.

805
00:56:14,500 --> 00:56:15,649
Eunho...

806
